node.text:
It really makes me sad to see how silent my fellow influencers in the community have been about Mental Health Awareness Month. When last year EVERYONE was talking about it... This issue hasn’t just disappeared. And I know this is something I myself should be talking about so much more than I do. Especially since this is something that I struggle with every single day. Living with Bipolar is one of the biggest challenges I’ve ever had to go through in my life. But I’m happy to announce that I’ve been off of my SSRI’s for over a year now. And while it’s still a challenge for me; I’m much happier not relying on prescription medication everyday 😁 I’m working much harder on finding more natural remedies to handle my tougher times. 
As much as people would look at having Bipolar as a set back, I’ve also found that it is my greatest super power. In my hypomanic states I am the most creative. 
And if my purpose as an influencer is to shed more light on these pressing issues & help inspire others who are struggling with similar issues; I’m more than happy with that🙏🏻🍃
I know times are tough. But please, don’t give up. Change is coming, and I promise it’s going to be more beautiful than anyone has ever imagined🕉
